The **Employee Pension Scheme (EPS)** is a pension scheme under EPFO where your employer contributes 8.33% of basic salary (up to a wage ceiling of ₹15,000/month) to build your pension corpus. The monthly pension at retirement = (Pensionable Salary × Pensionable Service) ÷ 70, where pensionable salary is the average of the last 60 months' salary.
